Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.61,0:00:30.00,中文,,0,0,0,,{\fs180\1c&HB0E4FF&\pos(2100,1850)\fsp80}第七集
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.61,0:00:30.00,中文,,0,0,0,,{\fs100\1c&H2D85FF&\pos(2100,2100)\fsp80}翻译：弥禾
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.89,0:02:23.89,中文,,0,0,0,,{\fs70\1c&HA5D5F1&\pos(3400,1900)}解说\N{\fs80}大卫·爱登堡
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.22,0:02:15.22,中文,,0,0,0,,{\fs180\1c&HB0E4FF&\pos(2100,1850)\fsp80}人类
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.72,0:00:32.72,中文,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.72,0:00:34.52,中文,,0,0,0,,吸鼻\N{\rEng}SNUFFLING
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.60,0:00:41.56,中文,,0,0,0,,尼泊尔索拉哈。\N{\rEng}Sauraha, Nepal.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.52,0:00:46.08,中文,,0,0,0,,鼻塞和咕噜声\N{\rEng}SNUFFLES AND GRUNTS
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.08,0:00:53.80,中文,,0,0,0,,喇叭蜂鸣声\N{\rEng}HORN BEEPS
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.04,0:00:58.40,中文,,0,0,0,,狗呜咽声\N{\rEng}DOG WHIMPERS
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.40,0:01:02.80,中文,,0,0,0,,这头犀牛并没有迷路。\N{\rEng}This rhino is not lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.16,0:01:10.24,中文,,0,0,0,,他正在去寻找食物的路上。\N{\rEng}He is on his way to find food.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.12,0:01:19.24,中文,,0,0,0,,为了得到它，他必须穿越一个新的陌生世界。\N{\rEng}To get it, he must travel through a new and alien world.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.20,0:01:30.64,中文,,0,0,0,,这头犀牛在其一生中\N{\rEng}This rhino in his lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.64,0:01:35.36,中文,,0,0,0,,比他的前几代人经历了更多的变化。\N{\rEng}has seen more changes than any of his previous generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.52,0:01:42.88,中文,,0,0,0,,在全球范围内，\N{\rEng}Across the globe,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.88,0:01:46.44,中文,,0,0,0,,现在各种动物都在争夺\N{\rEng}animals of all kinds are now contending
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.44,0:01:48.96,中文,,0,0,0,,一个新的优势物种...\N{\rEng}with one newly dominant species...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.40,0:01:51.96,中文,,0,0,0,,...我们。\N{\rEng}...us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.96,0:01:53.80,中文,,0,0,0,,喇叭声、警报声\N{\rEng}HORN BEEPS, SIREN WAILS
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.68,0:02:03.72,中文,,0,0,0,,像许多野生动物一样，他必须学习\N{\rEng}Like so many wild creatures, he's had to learn
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.72,0:02:07.96,中文,,0,0,0,,如何在人类世界中生存。\N{\rEng}how to live in the human world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.52,0:02:25.04,中文,,0,0,0,,一些动物\N{\rEng}Some animals
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.04,0:02:27.16,中文,,0,0,0,,改变了他们的行为\N{\rEng}have changed their behaviour
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.16,0:02:30.60,中文,,0,0,0,,充分利用我们之间的生活。\N{\rEng}to make the most out of living amongst us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.56,0:02:38.96,中文,,0,0,0,,这些长尾猕猴生活在巴厘岛。\N{\rEng}These long-tailed macaques live in Bali.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.84,0:02:52.44,中文,,0,0,0,,他们发展了新的兴趣\N{\rEng}They have developed new interests
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.44,0:02:55.44,中文,,0,0,0,,由人类访客带来。\N{\rEng}brought by human visitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.24,0:03:08.20,中文,,0,0,0,,每天早上，部队都会前往一座建筑物\N{\rEng}Every morning, the troop heads for a building
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.20,0:03:11.24,中文,,0,0,0,,在他们领土的中心。\N{\rEng}in the centre of their territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.24,0:03:24.68,中文,,0,0,0,,乌鲁瓦图寺。\N{\rEng}Uluwatu Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.68,0:03:26.52,中文,,0,0,0,,猕猴尖叫\N{\rEng}MACAQUES SCREECH
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.20,0:03:31.84,中文,,0,0,0,,每天都有成群结队的游客来到这里。\N{\rEng}Tourists come here every day - in crowds.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.72,0:03:39.44,中文,,0,0,0,,所以寺庙里充满了机会......\N{\rEng}So the temple grounds are full of opportunities...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.48,0:03:43.60,中文,,0,0,0,,...如果您知道去哪里寻找。\N{\rEng}...if you know where to look.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.44,0:04:12.52,中文,,0,0,0,,女人喘息\N{\rEng}WOMAN GASPS
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.52,0:04:15.52,中文,,0,0,0,,帽子的供应源源不断……\N{\rEng}There is a constant supply of hats...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.56,0:04:18.12,中文,,0,0,0,,...还有太阳镜。\N{\rEng}...and sunglasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.56,0:04:26.40,中文,,0,0,0,,如果你已经掌握了惊喜的元素......\N{\rEng}And if you've mastered the element of surprise...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.96,0:04:31.04,中文,,0,0,0,,……很容易得到它们。\N{\rEng}...it's easy to get them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.96,0:04:47.12,中文,,0,0,0,,但这个收获不是用来吃的。\N{\rEng}But this harvest is not for eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.12,0:04:50.96,中文,,0,0,0,,是为了讨价还价。\N{\rEng}It's for bargaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.40,0:05:00.76,中文,,0,0,0,,看起来像是公平交易。\N{\rEng}Seems like a fair trade.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.00,0:05:09.44,中文,,0,0,0,,但还有更大的回报\N{\rEng}But there are greater rewards to be had
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.44,0:05:12.48,中文,,0,0,0,,对于那些知道如何获得它们的人。\N{\rEng}for those who know how to get them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.16,0:05:15.96,中文,,0,0,0,,相机快门点击\N{\rEng}CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICK
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.12,0:05:21.96,中文,,0,0,0,,而这个老男人似乎正在做……\N{\rEng}And this old male appears to be doing...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.24,0:05:24.76,中文,,0,0,0,,...很好。\N{\rEng}...very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.76,0:05:33.96,中文,,0,0,0,,他和这支队伍中的其他长老\N{\rEng}He and the other elders in this troop
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.96,0:05:38.32,中文,,0,0,0,,既有经验又有知识。\N{\rEng}have both experience and knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.52,0:05:48.24,中文,,0,0,0,,他们在寺庙里工作了十多年，\N{\rEng}They've been working the temple for over ten years,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.24,0:05:50.88,中文,,0,0,0,,现在专注于大事......\N{\rEng}and now concentrate on the big stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.72,0:06:01.24,中文,,0,0,0,,...人类离不开的东西。\N{\rEng}...things that human beings just can't do without.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.00,0:06:06.72,中文,,0,0,0,,女人喘息\N{\rEng}WOMAN GASPS
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.36,0:06:12.36,中文,,0,0,0,,没有人愿意只穿一只鞋走路回家。\N{\rEng}No-one wants to walk home with just one shoe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.36,0:06:13.88,中文,,0,0,0,,女人喘息\N{\rEng}WOMAN GASPS
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.80,0:06:21.36,中文,,0,0,0,,这些老男孩已经等不及了\N{\rEng}And these old boys can't wait
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.36,0:06:25.08,中文,,0,0,0,,让他们掌握最新的技术。\N{\rEng}to get their hands on the latest tech.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.32,0:06:36.36,中文,,0,0,0,,她感叹道\N{\rEng}SHE EXCLAIMS
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.68,0:06:46.92,中文,,0,0,0,,他们发现我们根本无法生存\N{\rEng}They've worked out that we simply can't survive
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.92,0:06:49.16,中文,,0,0,0,,没有我们的手机...\N{\rEng}without our phones...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.04,0:06:54.72,中文,,0,0,0,,...或者我们的钱包。\N{\rEng}...or our wallets.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.76,0:07:04.12,中文,,0,0,0,,女人惊呼\N{\rEng}WOMAN EXCLAIMS
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.72,0:07:07.68,中文,,0,0,0,,猕猴尖叫声\N{\rEng}MACAQUE SCREECHES
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.28,0:07:15.04,中文,,0,0,0,,女人喘息\N{\rEng}WOMAN GASPS
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.04,0:07:17.20,中文,,0,0,0,,年长的男性都明白\N{\rEng}The older males understand
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.20,0:07:20.04,中文,,0,0,0,,年轻人还没有学到的东西......\N{\rEng}something the youngsters have yet to learn...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.72,0:07:26.24,中文,,0,0,0,,...交易的艺术。\N{\rEng}...the art of the deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.56,0:07:31.04,中文,,0,0,0,,一根香蕉？\N{\rEng}A banana?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.08,0:07:34.64,中文,,0,0,0,,你怎么敢！\N{\rEng}How dare you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.64,0:07:36.48,中文,,0,0,0,,猕猴尖叫声\N{\rEng}MACAQUE SCREECHES
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.88,0:07:39.48,中文,,0,0,0,,一块巧克力？\N{\rEng}A bar of chocolate?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.48,0:07:40.92,中文,,0,0,0,,这样更好。\N{\rEng}That's better.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.64,0:07:48.88,中文,,0,0,0,,真正的技巧在于谈判。\N{\rEng}The real skill is in the negotiations.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.28,0:07:58.12,中文,,0,0,0,,猕猴正在玩我们自己的游戏。\N{\rEng}The macaques are playing us at our own game.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.08,0:08:02.60,中文,,0,0,0,,他们要求...\N{\rEng}They demand...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.04,0:08:05.92,中文,,0,0,0,,...无论他们想要什么。\N{\rEng}...whatever they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.24,0:08:22.48,中文,,0,0,0,,人类已经传播到地球的每一个角落。\N{\rEng}Humanity has spread to every corner of the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.00,0:08:28.92,中文,,0,0,0,,我们已经成为自然的力量。\N{\rEng}We have become a force of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.92,0:08:42.16,中文,,0,0,0,,我们已经改变了80%的土地表面。\N{\rEng}We have altered 80% of the land's surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.44,0:08:53.84,中文,,0,0,0,,现在有八十亿人生活在这个星球上......\N{\rEng}Eight billion people now live on this planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.88,0:08:57.52,中文,,0,0,0,,...我们正在改变我们周围的世界\N{\rEng}...and we are changing the world around us
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.52,0:08:58.84,中文,,0,0,0,,以这样的速度...\N{\rEng}at such speed...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.88,0:09:06.80,中文,,0,0,0,,...对于动物来说，挑战是跟上。\N{\rEng}...that, for animals, the challenge is to keep up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.16,0:09:12.76,中文,,0,0,0,,纽约市。\N{\rEng}New York City.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.40,0:09:19.72,中文,,0,0,0,,蚂蚁。\N{\rEng}Ants.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.72,0:09:23.04,中文,,0,0,0,,人们认为这个特殊的物种已经到达这里\N{\rEng}This particular species is thought to have arrived here
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.04,0:09:25.52,中文,,0,0,0,,与第一批欧洲定居者一起。\N{\rEng}with the first European settlers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.24,0:09:32.00,中文,,0,0,0,,他们现在被称为路面蚂蚁\N{\rEng}They are now known as pavement ants
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.00,0:09:36.96,中文,,0,0,0,,因为他们几乎只住在我们的城镇里。\N{\rEng}because they live almost exclusively in our towns and cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.64,0:09:52.40,中文,,0,0,0,,他们因垃圾食品而蓬勃发展。\N{\rEng}And they're thriving because of junk food.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.16,0:09:56.48,中文,,0,0,0,,而在百老汇大街这里，\N{\rEng}And here on Broadway Avenue,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.48,0:09:58.48,中文,,0,0,0,,有很多。\N{\rEng}there's a lot of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.44,0:10:04.68,中文,,0,0,0,,这是每只路面蚂蚁所渴望的。\N{\rEng}This is what every pavement ant desires.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.00,0:10:10.52,中文,,0,0,0,,并且为了得到它...\N{\rEng}And to get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.40,0:10:15.96,中文,,0,0,0,,...蚂蚁利用城市的数千英里\N{\rEng}...the ants use the city's thousands of miles
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.96,0:10:17.60,中文,,0,0,0,,的地下隧道。\N{\rEng}of underground tunnels.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.32,0:10:29.72,中文,,0,0,0,,这名侦察兵正在逼近目标。\N{\rEng}This scout is closing in on its target.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.80,0:10:35.48,中文,,0,0,0,,但与他们共享人行道的动物\N{\rEng}But the animals with which they share the pavement
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.48,0:10:38.48,中文,,0,0,0,,是其体重的4000万倍...\N{\rEng}are 40 million times their weight...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.48,0:10:40.32,中文,,0,0,0,,脚步跺脚\N{\rEng}FOOTSTEPS STOMP
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.04,0:10:45.52,中文,,0,0,0,,……所以最好留在夹缝中。\N{\rEng}...so it's best to stay in the cracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.88,0:10:55.88,中文,,0,0,0,,大奖！\N{\rEng}Jackpot!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.88,0:10:57.88,中文,,0,0,0,,一座肉山。\N{\rEng}A meat mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.92,0:11:02.72,中文,,0,0,0,,对于一只蚂蚁来说，这项工作太大了。\N{\rEng}This is too big a job for just one ant.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.84,0:11:07.28,中文,,0,0,0,,这位工人是女性，\N{\rEng}This worker is female,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.28,0:11:10.16,中文,,0,0,0,,就像所有的蚁群一样，\N{\rEng}as they are in all ant colonies,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.16,0:11:15.12,中文,,0,0,0,,她会留下一条信息素的痕迹来标记一条路径。\N{\rEng}and she leaves a trail of pheromones to mark a path.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.64,0:11:21.72,中文,,0,0,0,,她和她遇到的每一个姐妹都有交流\N{\rEng}She communicates with every sister she meets
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.72,0:11:24.96,中文,,0,0,0,,当她回到巢穴时，\N{\rEng}as she returns to the nest,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.96,0:11:28.20,中文,,0,0,0,,街上的消息传得很快。\N{\rEng}and news on the street spreads fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.24,0:11:43.48,中文,,0,0,0,,这种超加工肉\N{\rEng}This ultra-processed meat
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.48,0:11:46.12,中文,,0,0,0,,和他们原来的食物有很大不同。\N{\rEng}is very different from their original food.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.96,0:11:52.20,中文,,0,0,0,,但他们的消化系统是他们成功的关键。\N{\rEng}But their digestive system is the key to their success.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.48,0:11:55.68,中文,,0,0,0,,它能够跟得上路\N{\rEng}It's able to keep up with the way
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.68,0:11:58.80,中文,,0,0,0,,人类不断改变饮食习惯。\N{\rEng}humans constantly change their diet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.08,0:12:05.88,中文,,0,0,0,,如今，他们吃的绝大多数东西\N{\rEng}Nowadays, the vast majority of what they eat
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.88,0:12:08.04,中文,,0,0,0,,来自人类食物。\N{\rEng}comes from human food.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.96,0:12:17.36,中文,,0,0,0,,仅在百老汇，\N{\rEng}On Broadway alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.36,0:12:20.12,中文,,0,0,0,,路面蚂蚁吃等量的食物\N{\rEng}pavement ants eat the equivalent
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.12,0:12:24.84,中文,,0,0,0,,每年生产 60,000 只热狗，数量惊人。\N{\rEng}of a staggering 60,000 hot dogs every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.08,0:12:30.88,中文,,0,0,0,,一个热狗的热量\N{\rEng}The calories in a single hot dog
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.88,0:12:32.44,中文,,0,0,0,,可以推动增长\N{\rEng}could fuel the growth
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.44,0:12:35.16,中文,,0,0,0,,整个蚁群一个月......\N{\rEng}of the entire ant colony for a month...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.16,0:12:39.64,中文,,0,0,0,,...如果他们能把它带回巢就好了。\N{\rEng}...if only they can get it back to the nest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.28,0:12:57.88,中文,,0,0,0,,但这种缓慢的工作使他们变得脆弱。\N{\rEng}But this slow work makes them vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.88,0:12:59.28,中文,,0,0,0,,鸽子咕咕\N{\rEng}PIGEON COOS
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.80,0:13:07.00,中文,,0,0,0,,他们并不是唯一偏爱快餐的人。\N{\rEng}They aren't the only ones partial to fast food.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.04,0:13:12.68,中文,,0,0,0,,这是一场将奖品带回家的竞赛。\N{\rEng}It's a race to get their prize home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.96,0:13:20.52,中文,,0,0,0,,可能会有损失...\N{\rEng}There may be losses...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.64,0:13:26.44,中文,,0,0,0,,......但整个殖民地现在将会蓬勃发展。\N{\rEng}...but the colony as a whole will now thrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.68,0:13:34.24,中文,,0,0,0,,事实上，路面蚂蚁在这里非常成功\N{\rEng}In fact, pavement ants are so successful here
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.24,0:13:37.84,中文,,0,0,0,,他们的人数比纽约人多 1,000 比 1。\N{\rEng}that they outnumber human New Yorkers 1,000 to 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.84,0:13:39.68,中文,,0,0,0,,鸽子首席运营官\N{\rEng}PIGEONS COO
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.88,0:13:47.88,中文,,0,0,0,,但人类世界的成功可能更难\N{\rEng}But success in the human world can be harder to achieve
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.88,0:13:51.80,中文,,0,0,0,,如果你的声誉领先于你。\N{\rEng}if your reputation precedes you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.12,0:14:03.68,中文,,0,0,0,,在印度这里，\N{\rEng}Here in India,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.68,0:14:07.92,中文,,0,0,0,,这条眼镜蛇正直奔一个村庄。\N{\rEng}this cobra is heading directly for a village.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.00,0:14:15.72,中文,,0,0,0,,它已经嗅到了猎物的气味。\N{\rEng}It has detected the scent of prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.24,0:14:19.92,中文,,0,0,0,,近两米长，\N{\rEng}Nearly two metres long,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.92,0:14:23.12,中文,,0,0,0,,它一口就有足够的毒液\N{\rEng}it has enough venom in a single bite
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.12,0:14:25.20,中文,,0,0,0,,杀死十个人。\N{\rEng}to kill ten people.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.32,0:14:42.20,中文,,0,0,0,,蛇咬伤是罪魁祸首\N{\rEng}Snake bites are responsible
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.20,0:14:45.36,中文,,0,0,0,,每年造成近 60,000 人死亡\N{\rEng}for nearly 60,000 deaths a year
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.36,0:14:47.12,中文,,0,0,0,,仅在印度。\N{\rEng}in India alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.40,0:14:57.96,中文,,0,0,0,,他们如此默默地旅行\N{\rEng}They travel so silently
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.96,0:15:01.48,中文,,0,0,0,,他们的存在常常未被发现。\N{\rEng}that their presence is often undetected.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.52,0:15:15.28,中文,,0,0,0,,而当他们狩猎时...\N{\rEng}And when they are hunting...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.56,0:15:19.08,中文,,0,0,0,,……没有他们不会去的地方。\N{\rEng}...there is no place they won't go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.00,0:15:41.40,中文,,0,0,0,,一只蟾蜍。\N{\rEng}A toad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.72,0:16:21.28,中文,,0,0,0,,它分叉的舌头的每一个尖端\N{\rEng}Each tip of its forked tongue
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.28,0:16:24.36,中文,,0,0,0,,收集猎物的化学信号\N{\rEng}collects chemical signals from the prey
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.36,0:16:27.20,中文,,0,0,0,,并有助于揭示其立场。\N{\rEng}and helps to reveal its position.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.64,0:16:34.32,中文,,0,0,0,,但近距离...\N{\rEng}But up close...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.32,0:16:35.64,中文,,0,0,0,,眼镜蛇嘶嘶声\N{\rEng}COBRA HISSES
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.64,0:16:37.92,中文,,0,0,0,,...蛇依靠运动\N{\rEng}...the snake relies on movement
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.92,0:16:41.00,中文,,0,0,0,,来精确定位猎物。\N{\rEng}to precisely locate its prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.68,0:16:51.80,中文,,0,0,0,,蟾蜍必须选择逃跑的时机。\N{\rEng}The toad must pick its moment to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.28,0:17:16.76,中文,,0,0,0,,每次接触地面的时候...\N{\rEng}Every time it touches the ground...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.00,0:17:21.32,中文,,0,0,0,,...蟾蜍留下气味。\N{\rEng}...the toad leaves behind a scent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.16,0:17:33.92,中文,,0,0,0,,它可以隐藏...\N{\rEng}It can hide...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.36,0:17:38.64,中文,,0,0,0,,……但这条踪迹会把蛇引向那里。\N{\rEng}...but the trail will lead the snake to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.96,0:18:19.16,中文,,0,0,0,,这些眼镜蛇不只是在这里狩猎。\N{\rEng}These cobras don't just hunt here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.16,0:18:21.04,中文,,0,0,0,,他们住在这里。\N{\rEng}They live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.64,0:18:27.68,中文,,0,0,0,,他们找到了印度教村民尊敬他们的家\N{\rEng}They have found a home where the Hindu villagers revere them
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.68,0:18:31.00,中文,,0,0,0,,并认为他们是半神。\N{\rEng}and consider them to be demigods.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.80,0:18:38.32,中文,,0,0,0,,值得注意的是，科学家认为这种耐受性\N{\rEng}Remarkably, scientists believe that this tolerance
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.32,0:18:41.08,中文,,0,0,0,,导致了蛇行为的改变。\N{\rEng}has led to a change in the snakes' behaviour.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.80,0:18:46.56,中文,,0,0,0,,他们移动得更慢\N{\rEng}They move more slowly
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.56,0:18:49.36,中文,,0,0,0,,如果受到干扰，则不太可能发起攻击。\N{\rEng}and are less likely to strike if disturbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.84,0:18:55.68,中文,,0,0,0,,地球上最可怕的动物之一\N{\rEng}One of the most feared animals on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.68,0:18:59.40,中文,,0,0,0,,已经找到了一个可以接受他们的地方\N{\rEng}has found a place where they are accepted
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.40,0:19:02.24,中文,,0,0,0,,并且可以与人类共存。\N{\rEng}and can coexist with human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.96,0:19:13.36,中文,,0,0,0,,但对于生活在人类世界的许多动物来说，\N{\rEng}But for many animals living in the human world,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.36,0:19:17.16,中文,,0,0,0,,保持低调是值得的。\N{\rEng}it pays to keep a low profile.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.12,0:19:24.56,中文,,0,0,0,,在澳大利亚墨尔本这里，\N{\rEng}Here in Melbourne, Australia,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.56,0:19:28.08,中文,,0,0,0,,有一种生物已经完善了伪装艺术。\N{\rEng}one creature has perfected the art of camouflage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.72,0:19:37.84,中文,,0,0,0,,一只蛙口小鸡。\N{\rEng}A frogmouth chick.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.00,0:19:43.04,中文,,0,0,0,,它的父亲白天帮忙把它藏起来。\N{\rEng}Its father helps to hide it during the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.96,0:19:49.60,中文,,0,0,0,,小鸡的叫声\N{\rEng}CHICK SQUAWKS
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.76,0:19:53.32,中文,,0,0,0,,它们是夜行性鸟类，\N{\rEng}They are nocturnal birds,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.32,0:19:55.92,中文,,0,0,0,,随着白天变成夜晚，\N{\rEng}and as day turns to night,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.92,0:19:58.76,中文,,0,0,0,,它的父母从阴影中走出来\N{\rEng}its parents come out of the shadows
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.76,0:20:02.44,中文,,0,0,0,,获得城市生活的回报。\N{\rEng}to reap the rewards of urban living.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.12,0:20:07.68,中文,,0,0,0,,城市灯光创造\N{\rEng}The city lights create
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.68,0:20:10.40,中文,,0,0,0,,狩猎条件优越。\N{\rEng}excellent conditions for hunting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.88,0:20:13.60,中文,,0,0,0,,城市里的每个夜晚\N{\rEng}Every night in the city
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.60,0:20:16.64,中文,,0,0,0,,如同满月时一样明亮。\N{\rEng}is as bright as when there is a full moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.20,0:20:23.36,中文,,0,0,0,,鸟叫声\N{\rEng}BIRD SQUAWKS
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.20,0:20:28.56,中文,,0,0,0,,所以城市蛙口经常...\N{\rEng}So city frogmouths often...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.60,0:20:31.96,中文,,0,0,0,,……他们的嘴都塞满了。\N{\rEng}...have their mouths full.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.36,0:20:41.64,中文,,0,0,0,,他成长得很快，今天他不会坐以待毙。\N{\rEng}He's growing fast, and today he just won't sit still.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.92,0:20:45.64,中文,,0,0,0,,狗叫声\N{\rEng}DOG BARKS
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.64,0:20:48.24,中文,,0,0,0,,现在他已经暴露了他的存在。\N{\rEng}And now he has revealed his presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.52,0:20:53.72,中文,,0,0,0,,蛙口行为的第一条规则是\N{\rEng}The first rule of frogmouth behaviour is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.72,0:20:56.40,中文,,0,0,0,,白天不要动。\N{\rEng}don't move in the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.40,0:21:00.04,中文,,0,0,0,,但这是蛙口一生中的一次\N{\rEng}But this is the one time in a frogmouth's life
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.04,0:21:04.48,中文,,0,0,0,,当想要飞翔的冲动根本无法抑制的时候。\N{\rEng}when the urge to fly simply cannot be suppressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.48,0:21:06.28,中文,,0,0,0,,狗裤\N{\rEng}DOG PANTS
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.28,0:21:08.76,中文,,0,0,0,,喙的声音、狗的叫声\N{\rEng}BEAK CLICKS, DOG BARKS
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.36,0:21:17.96,中文,,0,0,0,,但他还没有准备好离开家。\N{\rEng}But he's not ready to leave home just yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.76,0:21:24.56,中文,,0,0,0,,晚上来...\N{\rEng}Come night-time...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.72,0:21:27.76,中文,,0,0,0,,……他又饿了。\N{\rEng}...he's hungry again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.48,0:21:39.04,中文,,0,0,0,,他已经完全清醒了……\N{\rEng}He is wide awake...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.84,0:21:44.60,中文,,0,0,0,,...并想从他离开的地方开始。\N{\rEng}...and wants to take off where he left off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.56,0:21:53.24,中文,,0,0,0,,但他却受到了不必要的关注\N{\rEng}But he's getting unwanted attention,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.24,0:21:58.28,中文,,0,0,0,,这次他的父母不在附近保护他。\N{\rEng}and this time his parent is not nearby to protect him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.96,0:22:04.44,中文,,0,0,0,,人类带着宠物，\N{\rEng}Humans bring pets,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.44,0:22:09.96,中文,,0,0,0,,澳大利亚的猫每天杀死一百万只鸟。\N{\rEng}and cats in Australia kill a million birds a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.80,0:22:29.68,中文,,0,0,0,,领铃叮当响\N{\rEng}COLLAR BELL TINKLES
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.68,0:22:56.32,中文,,0,0,0,,他的第一次正确飞行。\N{\rEng}His first proper flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.84,0:23:04.32,中文,,0,0,0,,但除非他能找到一个安全的栖息地\N{\rEng}But unless he can find a safe place to roost,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.32,0:23:06.44,中文,,0,0,0,,他仍然处于危险之中。\N{\rEng}he is still in peril.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.60,0:23:17.12,中文,,0,0,0,,做好了。\N{\rEng}Made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.76,0:23:23.88,中文,,0,0,0,,但如果他要像大人一样在城市里生存，\N{\rEng}But if he is to survive in the city, like the adults,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.88,0:23:27.16,中文,,0,0,0,,他必须学会如何融入。\N{\rEng}he'll have to learn how to blend in.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.84,0:23:44.24,中文,,0,0,0,,有些动物就是这么大胆\N{\rEng}Some animals are so bold
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.24,0:23:46.96,中文,,0,0,0,,他们甚至不想隐藏。\N{\rEng}that they don't even try to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.64,0:23:55.16,中文,,0,0,0,,在建筑群中看到大型掠食者是罕见的景象。\N{\rEng}To see a large predator in the built-up world is a rare sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.76,0:24:01.80,中文,,0,0,0,,在北美的太浩湖，\N{\rEng}And here in Lake Tahoe, in North America,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.80,0:24:06.04,中文,,0,0,0,,这些黑熊特别大……\N{\rEng}these black bears are particularly big...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.64,0:24:12.04,中文,,0,0,0,,……他们正前往市中心。\N{\rEng}...and they're heading right to the centre of town.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.04,0:24:13.48,中文,,0,0,0,,熊咀嚼物\N{\rEng}BEAR CHOMPS
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.48,0:24:16.16,中文,,0,0,0,,冬天即将来临，\N{\rEng}Winter is approaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.16,0:24:19.16,中文,,0,0,0,,这些熊需要增加尽可能多的体重\N{\rEng}and these bears need to put on as much weight as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.16,0:24:21.20,中文,,0,0,0,,在雪到来之前。\N{\rEng}before the snow arrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.00,0:24:27.44,中文,,0,0,0,,这是一个饱餐一顿的好地方。\N{\rEng}This is a great place to gorge.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.64,0:24:34.04,中文,,0,0,0,,喇叭声\N{\rEng}HORN BLARES
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.04,0:24:36.04,中文,,0,0,0,,现在是熊国。\N{\rEng}It's now bear country.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.04,0:24:39.08,中文,,0,0,0,,栅栏吱吱作响\N{\rEng}FENCE CREAKS
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.08,0:24:41.64,中文,,0,0,0,,何必为了一顿饭而苦苦挣扎……\N{\rEng}Why struggle for a meal...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.92,0:24:46.00,中文,,0,0,0,,...当你可以过马路时...\N{\rEng}...when you can cross the street...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.28,0:24:49.04,中文,,0,0,0,,……外卖？\N{\rEng}...for a takeaway?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.92,0:24:58.28,中文,,0,0,0,,这里有这么多食物\N{\rEng}There's so much food here
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.28,0:25:01.48,中文,,0,0,0,,有些熊重 50%\N{\rEng}that some of the bears are 50% heavier
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.48,0:25:03.32,中文,,0,0,0,,比他们的乡下表兄弟。\N{\rEng}than their country cousins.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.00,0:25:10.12,中文,,0,0,0,,但为什么停在这里呢？\N{\rEng}But why stop here?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.72,0:25:15.40,中文,,0,0,0,,有些熊只是想在里面吃饭。\N{\rEng}Some bears just want to dine in.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.76,0:25:21.56,中文,,0,0,0,,女人喘息\N{\rEng}WOMAN GASPS
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.68,0:25:28.08,中文,,0,0,0,,少数幸运者能够从人类世界轻松获得一顿美餐。\N{\rEng}A lucky few are able to get an easy meal from the human world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.44,0:25:34.28,中文,,0,0,0,,但是当我们冒险到自然世界寻找食物时......\N{\rEng}But when WE venture to the natural world in search of food...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.92,0:25:38.88,中文,,0,0,0,,……收获的规模不同。\N{\rEng}...the harvest is on a different scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.08,0:25:42.12,中文,,0,0,0,,短短四十年的时间，\N{\rEng}In just four decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.12,0:25:46.68,中文,,0,0,0,,捕鱼使鱼类数量减少了一半...\N{\rEng}fishing reduced fish populations by half...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.44,0:25:51.96,中文,,0,0,0,,...给海洋掠食者带来了很大的问题\N{\rEng}...and created great problems for the ocean predators
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.96,0:25:54.64,中文,,0,0,0,,曾经有过这样的食物。\N{\rEng}that once had such food to themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.84,0:25:59.24,中文,,0,0,0,,船的号角吹响\N{\rEng}SHIP'S HORN BLOWS
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.44,0:26:04.76,中文,,0,0,0,,在温哥华岛海岸附近，\N{\rEng}Off the coast of Vancouver Island,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.76,0:26:07.80,中文,,0,0,0,,座头鲸栖息于水域\N{\rEng}humpback whales inhabit waters
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.80,0:26:10.76,中文,,0,0,0,,那里的鲱鱼被过度捕捞。\N{\rEng}where herring have been overfished.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.64,0:26:20.68,中文,,0,0,0,,然而，座头鲸以其聪明才智而闻名。\N{\rEng}Humpbacks, however, are renowned for their ingenuity.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.64,0:26:27.04,中文,,0,0,0,,12年前，一位名叫Conger的成年男性\N{\rEng}12 years ago, an adult male called Conger
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.04,0:26:30.60,中文,,0,0,0,,采用了全新的喂养方式。\N{\rEng}adopted a totally new way of feeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.88,0:26:35.08,中文,,0,0,0,,当水中鱼的密度较低时，\N{\rEng}When the density of fish in the water is low,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.08,0:26:37.64,中文,,0,0,0,,鸟儿们潜入水中捕捉它们......\N{\rEng}and birds are diving to catch them...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.76,0:26:41.76,中文,,0,0,0,,...座头鲸张开嘴\N{\rEng}...the humpback opens its mouth
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.76,0:26:45.84,中文,,0,0,0,,并创造一个被鱼误认为庇护所的空间。\N{\rEng}and creates a space that the fish mistake for shelter.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.00,0:26:54.92,中文,,0,0,0,,鱼儿游在...\N{\rEng}The fish swim in...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.88,0:27:00.96,中文,,0,0,0,,……陷阱就关闭了。\N{\rEng}...and the trap is closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.16,0:27:11.56,中文,,0,0,0,,海康格鲸是第一头被发现这样做的座头鲸。\N{\rEng}Conger was the first humpback whale to be seen doing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.72,0:27:19.48,中文,,0,0,0,,现在该地区有 30 头鲸鱼使用同样的技术。\N{\rEng}Now 30 whales in the area use this same technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.40,0:27:28.60,中文,,0,0,0,,这里的座头鲸数量正在增长，\N{\rEng}The population of humpbacks here is growing,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.60,0:27:31.16,中文,,0,0,0,,你可能认为这会\N{\rEng}and you might think that this would
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.16,0:27:33.80,中文,,0,0,0,,进一步减少鱼类资源，\N{\rEng}reduce fish stocks even more,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.80,0:27:36.68,中文,,0,0,0,,但人们认为令人惊讶的事情正在发生。\N{\rEng}but something surprising is thought to be happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.32,0:27:42.52,中文,,0,0,0,,这些微小的浮游植物是食物链的基础\N{\rEng}These tiny phytoplankton are the basis of the food chain
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.52,0:27:46.12,中文,,0,0,0,,并且需要重要的成分才能生长。\N{\rEng}and need a vital ingredient to grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.48,0:27:49.56,中文,,0,0,0,,铁。\N{\rEng}Iron.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.32,0:28:00.52,中文,,0,0,0,,鲸鱼的粪便富含铁...\N{\rEng}Whale faeces are rich in iron...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.84,0:28:06.52,中文,,0,0,0,,...大鲸鱼大量生产它...\N{\rEng}...and great whales produce it in enormous quantities...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.96,0:28:13.52,中文,,0,0,0,,...所以浮游植物繁盛，鲱鱼以它为食。\N{\rEng}...so the phytoplankton flourishes, and herring feed on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.32,0:28:18.68,中文,,0,0,0,,事实上，鲸鱼的粪便\N{\rEng}Whale faeces, in fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.68,0:28:22.32,中文,,0,0,0,,正在帮助恢复整个生态系统。\N{\rEng}are helping to restore the whole ecosystem.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.48,0:28:28.16,中文,,0,0,0,,鲱鱼吸引海鸟，\N{\rEng}The herring attract seabirds,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.16,0:28:31.72,中文,,0,0,0,,潜水的鸟从下面攻击它们，\N{\rEng}diving birds attack them from beneath,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.72,0:28:35.52,中文,,0,0,0,,海鸥和海鸥从上面俯冲到它们身上。\N{\rEng}and gulls and shearwaters dive on them from above.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.00,0:28:41.40,中文,,0,0,0,,即使是秃鹰也能从这场丰盛的盛宴中受益。\N{\rEng}Even bald eagles benefit from this rich feast.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.00,0:29:23.60,中文,,0,0,0,,令人惊讶的是，尽管康格鲸和所有其他鲸鱼\N{\rEng}Astonishingly, even though Conger and all the other whales
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.60,0:29:26.24,中文,,0,0,0,,正在大口吃鱼，\N{\rEng}are feasting on fish,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.24,0:29:30.96,中文,,0,0,0,,他们在海洋施肥方面的作用是如此有影响力\N{\rEng}their role in fertilising the ocean is so influential
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.96,0:29:35.12,中文,,0,0,0,,这里的鲱鱼数量实际上预计会增加。\N{\rEng}that herring numbers here are actually predicted to increase.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.24,0:29:46.60,中文,,0,0,0,,以及它们在恢复环境活力方面发挥的作用......\N{\rEng}And the role they play in rejuvenating the environment...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.36,0:29:56.56,中文,,0,0,0,,......对人类世界产生更大的影响。\N{\rEng}...is having an even greater impact on the human world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.36,0:30:08.40,中文,,0,0,0,,繁盛的浮游生物也收集碳\N{\rEng}The flourishing plankton also collects carbon
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.40,0:30:10.80,中文,,0,0,0,,从大气中，就像树一样......\N{\rEng}from the atmosphere, just as trees do...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.28,0:30:17.04,中文,,0,0,0,,...如此之多以至于每头鲸鱼\N{\rEng}...so much so that each great whale
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.04,0:30:22.24,中文,,0,0,0,,与拥有 30,000 棵树的森林具有相同的影响。\N{\rEng}has the same impact as a forest of 30,000 trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.88,0:30:32.80,中文,,0,0,0,,我们的大鲸鱼曾经被猎杀......\N{\rEng}Our great whales were once hunted...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.80,0:30:38.04,中文,,0,0,0,,...如果它们恢复到捕鲸前的数量，\N{\rEng}...and if they return to their pre-whaling numbers,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.04,0:30:41.76,中文,,0,0,0,,估计这相当于种草了\N{\rEng}it's estimated that this would be equivalent to planting
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.76,0:30:45.28,中文,,0,0,0,,超过300亿棵树。\N{\rEng}over 30 billion trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.12,0:31:03.72,中文,,0,0,0,,鲸鱼现在被认为对人类有益。\N{\rEng}Whales are now being recognised as benefiting humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.12,0:31:10.92,中文,,0,0,0,,但对于大多数大型动物来说\N{\rEng}But for most large animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.92,0:31:15.20,中文,,0,0,0,,与人类的竞争会带来冲突。\N{\rEng}competition with humans brings conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.20,0:31:21.60,中文,,0,0,0,,这头六吨重的非洲公象正处于鼎盛时期。\N{\rEng}This six-tonne African bull elephant is in his prime.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.60,0:31:23.48,中文,,0,0,0,,大象咕噜声\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT GRUNTS
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.40,0:31:28.80,中文,,0,0,0,,为了获得女性赢得战斗的最佳机会，\N{\rEng}To stand the best chance of winning fights for females,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.80,0:31:30.72,中文,,0,0,0,,他需要变得很大。\N{\rEng}he needs to be big.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.64,0:31:37.04,中文,,0,0,0,,他能闻到附近有营养丰富的食物的味道。\N{\rEng}He can smell highly nutritious food is near.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.72,0:31:48.84,中文,,0,0,0,,但跨越界限才能到达\N{\rEng}But crossing the boundary to reach it
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.84,0:31:51.28,中文,,0,0,0,,这是一次危险的旅程。\N{\rEng}is a dangerous journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.20,0:32:00.68,中文,,0,0,0,,他必须等待黑暗的掩护。\N{\rEng}He must wait for the cover of darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.84,0:32:07.92,中文,,0,0,0,,火爆裂纹\N{\rEng}FIRE CRACKLES
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.28,0:32:16.08,中文,,0,0,0,,这些肯尼亚农民正在为即将到来的夜晚做准备。\N{\rEng}These Kenyan farmers are preparing for the night ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.12,0:32:21.44,中文,,0,0,0,,他们必须每天晚上看守他们的庄稼\N{\rEng}They have had to guard their crops every night
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.44,0:32:23.04,中文,,0,0,0,,过去两个月。\N{\rEng}for the last two months.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.84,0:32:29.52,中文,,0,0,0,,距离收获只剩两天了，\N{\rEng}With only two days until harvest,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.52,0:32:32.72,中文,,0,0,0,,这是一个关键时刻。\N{\rEng}this is a critical time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.52,0:32:41.00,中文,,0,0,0,,男人喊叫\N{\rEng}MAN SHOUTS
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.00,0:32:42.48,中文,,0,0,0,,在一个晚上，\N{\rEng}In a single night,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.48,0:32:45.80,中文,,0,0,0,,一头公象可以毁掉整个庄稼\N{\rEng}a bull elephant can destroy the entire crops
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.80,0:32:47.68,中文,,0,0,0,,由十个农民生产。\N{\rEng}produced by ten farmers.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.68,0:32:49.60,中文,,0,0,0,,喊叫\N{\rEng}SHOUTING
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.60,0:32:51.56,中文,,0,0,0,,大象咆哮\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT ROARS
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.12,0:32:57.56,中文,,0,0,0,,男人喊叫\N{\rEng}MAN SHOUTS
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.36,0:33:07.08,中文,,0,0,0,,但他冒着巨大的风险。\N{\rEng}But he's taking a huge risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.08,0:33:08.36,中文,,0,0,0,,大象咆哮\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT ROARS
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.36,0:33:10.52,中文,,0,0,0,,喊叫\N{\rEng}SHOUTING
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.52,0:33:23.40,中文,,0,0,0,,大象的尖叫声\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT SCREECHES
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.40,0:33:25.80,中文,,0,0,0,,喊叫\N{\rEng}SHOUTING
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.80,0:33:27.32,中文,,0,0,0,,大象咆哮\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT ROARS
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.92,0:33:33.28,中文,,0,0,0,,大象喇叭\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT TRUMPETS
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.24,0:33:38.72,中文,,0,0,0,,大象咆哮\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT ROARS
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.44,0:33:43.76,中文,,0,0,0,,大象咆哮\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT ROARS
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.76,0:33:46.20,中文,,0,0,0,,他的身高是人类的两倍...\N{\rEng}He's twice the height of a man...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.20,0:33:48.64,中文,,0,0,0,,大象咆哮\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT ROARS
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.64,0:33:50.68,中文,,0,0,0,,……他不会轻易退缩。\N{\rEng}...and he won't back down easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.68,0:33:52.40,中文,,0,0,0,,喊叫\N{\rEng}SHOUTING
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.88,0:33:59.84,中文,,0,0,0,,人类与野生动物的冲突日复一日地发生。\N{\rEng}This human-wildlife conflict happens night after night.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.40,0:34:05.28,中文,,0,0,0,,每年，它都会夺走生命\N{\rEng}And each year, it takes the lives
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.28,0:34:10.24,中文,,0,0,0,,仅在肯尼亚就有多达 200 头大象和 20 个人。\N{\rEng}of up to 200 elephants and 20 people in Kenya alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.20,0:34:13.56,中文,,0,0,0,,低沉的隆隆声\N{\rEng}LOW RUMBLING
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.56,0:34:16.84,中文,,0,0,0,,这种对峙可能是致命的。\N{\rEng}This standoff is potentially lethal.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.64,0:34:22.04,中文,,0,0,0,,农民们不得不打电话求助\N{\rEng}The farmers have had to call for help
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.04,0:34:25.16,中文,,0,0,0,,来自经验丰富的护林员团队。\N{\rEng}from a team of highly experienced rangers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.24,0:34:43.60,中文,,0,0,0,,虽然他们全副武装，\N{\rEng}Although they're armed,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.60,0:34:47.04,中文,,0,0,0,,他们的任务是将大象赶出田野\N{\rEng}their task is to drive the elephant out of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.04,0:34:48.60,中文,,0,0,0,,而不伤害它。\N{\rEng}without harming it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.72,0:34:54.12,中文,,0,0,0,,但公牛决心...\N{\rEng}But the bull is determined...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.12,0:34:56.04,中文,,0,0,0,,大象喇叭\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT TRUMPETS
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.04,0:34:57.84,中文,,0,0,0,,……坚守阵地。\N{\rEng}...to hold ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.88,0:35:02.76,中文,,0,0,0,,低沉的隆隆声\N{\rEng}LOW RUMBLING
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.76,0:35:06.00,中文,,0,0,0,,护林员将不得不靠近......\N{\rEng}The rangers will have to get closer...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.00,0:35:08.04,中文,,0,0,0,,大象咆哮\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT ROARS
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.04,0:35:09.48,中文,,0,0,0,,...徒步。\N{\rEng}...on foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.00,0:35:13.12,中文,,0,0,0,,大象咆哮\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT GROWLS
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.12,0:35:21.84,中文,,0,0,0,,低沉的隆隆声\N{\rEng}LOW RUMBLING
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.12,0:35:29.20,中文,,0,0,0,,护林员必须采取...爆竹爆炸声\N{\rEng}The rangers have to resort... FIRECRACKER BANGS
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.20,0:35:32.56,中文,,0,0,0,,大象咆哮......鞭炮声。\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT GROWLS ...to firecrackers.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.20,0:35:38.04,中文,,0,0,0,,鞭炮声、大象吼声\N{\rEng}FIRECRACKER BANGS, ELEPHANT ROARS
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.84,0:35:47.64,中文,,0,0,0,,大象咆哮\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT GROWLS
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.52,0:35:53.64,中文,,0,0,0,,公牛被赶出了这片土地......\N{\rEng}The bull is driven from this field...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.64,0:35:54.96,中文,,0,0,0,,大象咆哮\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT GROWLS
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.96,0:35:57.72,中文,,0,0,0,,……然后撤退到灌木丛深处。\N{\rEng}...and retreats deep into the bush.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.40,0:36:09.04,中文,,0,0,0,,对于这头公牛来说幸运的是，\N{\rEng}Fortunately for this bull,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.04,0:36:12.52,中文,,0,0,0,,战斗已经和平解决。\N{\rEng}the battle has been resolved peacefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.52,0:36:16.60,中文,,0,0,0,,诸如此类的努力减少了大象被杀的情况，\N{\rEng}And efforts like these are seeing fewer elephants killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.60,0:36:20.96,中文,,0,0,0,,肯尼亚的人口又开始增加。\N{\rEng}and their population in Kenya is starting to rise again.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.56,0:36:24.76,中文,,0,0,0,,但与野生动物发生冲突\N{\rEng}But conflict with wildlife
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.76,0:36:27.56,中文,,0,0,0,,现在正在以更大的规模发生\N{\rEng}is now occurring on a far greater scale
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.56,0:36:28.76,中文,,0,0,0,,作为结果\N{\rEng}as a consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.76,0:36:31.64,中文,,0,0,0,,我们正在改变世界气候的方式。\N{\rEng}of the way we are changing the world's climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.52,0:36:37.00,中文,,0,0,0,,一些干旱地区\N{\rEng}Some arid regions
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.00,0:36:40.72,中文,,0,0,0,,现在正在经历异常高的降雨量。\N{\rEng}are now experiencing unusually high rainfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.40,0:36:47.92,中文,,0,0,0,,这对农作物生长有好处\N{\rEng}And that is good for growing crops
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.92,0:36:50.04,中文,,0,0,0,,这里是非洲东北部。\N{\rEng}here in northeastern Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.44,0:36:55.40,中文,,0,0,0,,但这也是完美的条件\N{\rEng}But it's also the perfect conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.40,0:36:58.04,中文,,0,0,0,,对于一种特定的昆虫。\N{\rEng}for one particular insect.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.08,0:37:15.36,中文,,0,0,0,,沙漠蝗虫。\N{\rEng}Desert locusts.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.92,0:37:22.32,中文,,0,0,0,,它们通常是独居动物，\N{\rEng}They're normally solitary creatures,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.32,0:37:25.20,中文,,0,0,0,,但大量地从沙子里冒出来\N{\rEng}but emerging from the sand in great numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.20,0:37:27.96,中文,,0,0,0,,引发剧烈的身体变化。\N{\rEng}triggers a dramatic physical change.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.60,0:37:37.72,中文,,0,0,0,,它们变成鲜艳的黄色\N{\rEng}They turn a vivid yellow
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.72,0:37:39.80,中文,,0,0,0,,并变得高度社交。\N{\rEng}and become highly social.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.40,0:37:45.60,中文,,0,0,0,,他们在一起就是一支不可阻挡的军队。\N{\rEng}Together, they are an unstoppable army.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.88,0:37:51.56,中文,,0,0,0,,步行，他们每天可以走一英里。\N{\rEng}On foot, they can cover a mile a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.32,0:38:00.48,中文,,0,0,0,,但他们只能以这种方式走这么远。\N{\rEng}But they can only go so far in this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.40,0:38:08.44,中文,,0,0,0,,他们需要找到高度。\N{\rEng}They need to find height.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.36,0:38:23.92,中文,,0,0,0,,在这里，他们开始了最后的转变。\N{\rEng}Up here, they begin their final transformation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.44,0:38:34.08,中文,,0,0,0,,通常，需要单个昆虫\N{\rEng}Normally, it takes an individual insect
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.08,0:38:37.36,中文,,0,0,0,,至少要一个月才能成为有翅膀的成年人……\N{\rEng}at least a month to become a winged adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.88,0:38:42.72,中文,,0,0,0,,...但在他们的社会形式中，他们的发展速度加快。\N{\rEng}...but in their social form, their development speeds up.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.56,0:38:50.24,中文,,0,0,0,,压制\N{\rEng}SQUELCHING
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.48,0:39:02.76,中文,,0,0,0,,现在他们所需要的只是让翅膀变硬。\N{\rEng}Now all they need is for their wings to harden.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.24,0:39:18.72,中文,,0,0,0,,一旦升空，他们一天可以飞行 60 英里。\N{\rEng}Once airborne, they can travel 60 miles in a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.56,0:39:44.04,中文,,0,0,0,,蜂群合并，成为瘟疫。\N{\rEng}Swarms merge and they become a plague.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.72,0:39:52.28,中文,,0,0,0,,这其中包含了数十亿个人，\N{\rEng}This one contains billions of individuals,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.28,0:39:54.48,中文,,0,0,0,,一天吃那么多\N{\rEng}and eats as much in a day
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.48,0:39:58.08,中文,,0,0,0,,相当于德国的全部人口。\N{\rEng}as the entire population of Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.12,0:40:28.20,中文,,0,0,0,,今天在非洲东北部，\N{\rEng}Today in northeastern Africa,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.20,0:40:31.64,中文,,0,0,0,,由于气候变化...\N{\rEng}as a consequence of climate change...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.64,0:40:35.20,中文,,0,0,0,,...毁灭性的蝗虫激增\N{\rEng}...devastating surges of locusts
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.20,0:40:37.52,中文,,0,0,0,,变得越来越频繁。\N{\rEng}are becoming more frequent.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.12,0:40:52.36,中文,,0,0,0,,两个世界正在碰撞。\N{\rEng}Two worlds are colliding.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.52,0:41:05.56,中文,,0,0,0,,人类无意中创造了这样的条件\N{\rEng}Unintentionally, humanity has created exactly the conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.56,0:41:10.04,中文,,0,0,0,,导致该物种数量爆炸。\N{\rEng}that cause this species to explode in numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.44,0:41:38.20,中文,,0,0,0,,但另一群动物却看到了\N{\rEng}But another group of animals has seen
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.20,0:41:40.68,中文,,0,0,0,,更大幅度的上升\N{\rEng}an even more dramatic rise
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.68,0:41:43.52,中文,,0,0,0,,作为我们行动的结果。\N{\rEng}as a consequence of OUR actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.44,0:41:50.64,中文,,0,0,0,,我们增加了一些物种的数量\N{\rEng}We have increased the numbers of a few species
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.64,0:41:52.68,中文,,0,0,0,,几乎是天文数字。\N{\rEng}almost astronomically.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.68,0:41:54.44,中文,,0,0,0,,小鸡叽叽喳喳\N{\rEng}CHICKS CHEEP
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.44,0:41:55.88,中文,,0,0,0,,按重量计算，\N{\rEng}By weight,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.88,0:41:59.92,中文,,0,0,0,,现在世界上70%的鸟类是鸡\N{\rEng}70% of the world's birds are now chickens
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.92,0:42:02.56,中文,,0,0,0,,或其他家禽。\N{\rEng}or other domesticated fowl.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.20,0:42:18.12,中文,,0,0,0,,我们每年饲养 700 亿头农场动物......\N{\rEng}We rear 70 billion farm animals each year...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.12,0:42:19.68,中文,,0,0,0,,猪咕噜声\N{\rEng}PIG GRUNTS
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.68,0:42:22.48,中文,,0,0,0,,……他们每个人都需要喂养。\N{\rEng}...and every one of them needs feeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.80,0:42:25.76,中文,,0,0,0,,生产食物\N{\rEng}Producing the food
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.76,0:42:29.00,中文,,0,0,0,,对于如此数量的家养动物\N{\rEng}for such numbers of domesticated animals
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.00,0:42:32.76,中文,,0,0,0,,对自然世界产生着深远的影响。\N{\rEng}is having a profound impact on the natural world.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.76,0:42:34.72,中文,,0,0,0,,鸡叫声\N{\rEng}CHICKENS CLUCK
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.84,0:42:43.40,中文,,0,0,0,,亚马逊雨林——\N{\rEng}The Amazon rainforest -
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.40,0:42:46.24,中文,,0,0,0,,是印度面积的两倍。\N{\rEng}twice the size of India.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.56,0:42:50.08,中文,,0,0,0,,真是太丰富了，\N{\rEng}It's so rich,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.08,0:42:54.76,中文,,0,0,0,,它包含了地球上十分之一的物种。\N{\rEng}it contains one in every ten species on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.88,0:43:00.60,中文,,0,0,0,,这里是这只树懒和她十个月大的孩子的家。\N{\rEng}And it's home to this sloth and her ten-month-old baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.76,0:43:11.44,中文,,0,0,0,,他出生在一个环境\N{\rEng}He was born into an environment
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.44,0:43:14.56,中文,,0,0,0,,几乎没有受到人类的影响。\N{\rEng}virtually untouched by humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.20,0:43:21.24,中文,,0,0,0,,电锯嗡嗡声\N{\rEng}CHAINSAW BUZZES
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.20,0:43:28.64,中文,,0,0,0,,但现在人类甚至也声称拥有这个空间。\N{\rEng}But now human beings are claiming even this space.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.28,0:44:00.40,中文,,0,0,0,,年复一年，我们清理了超过 200 万公顷的土地\N{\rEng}Year after year, we clear over two million hectares
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.40,0:44:02.24,中文,,0,0,0,,亚马逊森林——\N{\rEng}of the Amazon forest -
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.24,0:44:05.72,中文,,0,0,0,,面积相当于威尔士那么大。\N{\rEng}an area the size of Wales.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.52,0:44:14.92,中文,,0,0,0,,我们几乎使用了所有这些\N{\rEng}And we use nearly all of it
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.92,0:44:17.48,中文,,0,0,0,,为牛腾出更多空间...\N{\rEng}to make more space for cattle...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.68,0:44:22.60,中文,,0,0,0,,...并种植大豆来喂养我们的牲畜。\N{\rEng}...and to grow soya to feed our livestock.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.28,0:44:31.44,中文,,0,0,0,,如今，栖息地破坏是最大的问题\N{\rEng}Today, habitat destruction is the biggest problem
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.44,0:44:35.04,中文,,0,0,0,,我们为世界各地的野生动物创造了。\N{\rEng}we have created for wildlife around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.72,0:44:39.88,中文,,0,0,0,,树枝沙沙作响\N{\rEng}BRANCHES RUSTLE
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.12,0:44:44.48,中文,,0,0,0,,这只豪猪在火灾中幸存下来......\N{\rEng}This porcupine has survived the fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.64,0:44:49.68,中文,,0,0,0,,……正在获救。\N{\rEng}...and is being rescued.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.44,0:45:03.12,中文,,0,0,0,,它正在被迁移到原始森林。\N{\rEng}It's being relocated to pristine forests.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.64,0:45:11.40,中文,,0,0,0,,这将是它的新家。\N{\rEng}This will be its new home.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.28,0:45:21.52,中文,,0,0,0,,只有少数幸运的动物\N{\rEng}Only a fortunate few animals
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.52,0:45:25.00,中文,,0,0,0,,正在被给予这样的第二次机会。\N{\rEng}are being given such a second chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.60,0:45:51.80,中文,,0,0,0,,健康的自然世界不仅对野生动物至关重要……\N{\rEng}A healthy natural world is not only vital for wildlife...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.00,0:45:56.88,中文,,0,0,0,,...但为了我们自己的存在。\N{\rEng}...but for our own very existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.80,0:46:06.60,中文,,0,0,0,,我们必须以某种方式找到纠正平衡的方法。\N{\rEng}Somehow we must find ways to redress the balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.92,0:46:18.44,中文,,0,0,0,,目前，绝大多数农业用地，\N{\rEng}Currently, the vast majority of agricultural land,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.44,0:46:20.68,中文,,0,0,0,,超过75%，\N{\rEng}more than 75%,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.68,0:46:23.36,中文,,0,0,0,,用于饲养牲畜，\N{\rEng}is used to raise livestock,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.36,0:46:25.92,中文,,0,0,0,,这是非常低效的。\N{\rEng}and this is very inefficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.80,0:46:31.76,中文,,0,0,0,,有解决方案。\N{\rEng}There are solutions.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.56,0:46:36.40,中文,,0,0,0,,一是考虑我们吃什么。\N{\rEng}One is considering what we eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.92,0:46:49.20,中文,,0,0,0,,如果我们不再吃肉类和奶制品\N{\rEng}If we shift away from eating meat and dairy
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.20,0:46:52.40,中文,,0,0,0,,并转向植物性饮食，\N{\rEng}and move towards a plant-based diet,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.40,0:46:57.16,中文,,0,0,0,,然后太阳的能量直接用于种植我们的食物。\N{\rEng}then the sun's energy goes directly into growing our food.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.44,0:47:06.96,中文,,0,0,0,,因为这样效率更高\N{\rEng}And because that's so much more efficient,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.96,0:47:10.52,中文,,0,0,0,,我们仍然可以生产足够的食物来养活我们，\N{\rEng}we could still produce enough to feed us,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.52,0:47:14.36,中文,,0,0,0,,但这样做需要使用四分之一的土地。\N{\rEng}but do so using a quarter of the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.32,0:47:22.88,中文,,0,0,0,,这可以腾出相当于美国那么大的面积，\N{\rEng}This could free up an area the size of the United States,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.88,0:47:28.52,中文,,0,0,0,,中国、欧盟和澳大利亚联合...\N{\rEng}China, the European Union and Australia combined...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.88,0:47:35.88,中文,,0,0,0,,...然后可以回归自然的空间。\N{\rEng}...space that could then be given back to nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.32,0:47:43.96,中文,,0,0,0,,人类的创新也许能够\N{\rEng}And human innovations may be able
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.96,0:47:46.68,中文,,0,0,0,,为野生动物做更多的事情。\N{\rEng}to do even more for wildlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.68,0:47:54.20,中文,,0,0,0,,高科技农场现在垂直种植植物，\N{\rEng}High-tech farms now grow plants vertically,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.20,0:47:59.52,中文,,0,0,0,,产量是同一地区种植粮食的 350 倍。\N{\rEng}yielding up to 350 times the food grown in the same area.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.68,0:48:07.08,中文,,0,0,0,,这是我们已有的众多解决方案之一，\N{\rEng}This is one of many solutions we already have,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.08,0:48:10.36,中文,,0,0,0,,其他的肯定也即将出现。\N{\rEng}and others are surely on the horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.92,0:48:26.20,中文,,0,0,0,,寻找保护地球上所有生命的方法\N{\rEng}To find ways to protect all life on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.20,0:48:31.32,中文,,0,0,0,,意味着重新想象我们未来如何在这个星球上生活。\N{\rEng}means reimagining how we live on this planet in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.32,0:48:33.16,中文,,0,0,0,,人类的聪明才智，\N{\rEng}Human ingenuity,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.16,0:48:36.60,中文,,0,0,0,,我们寻找解决方案的非凡能力，\N{\rEng}our extraordinary ability to find solutions,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.60,0:48:39.96,中文,,0,0,0,,让我希望我们能做到。\N{\rEng}gives me hope that we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.96,0:48:42.28,中文,,0,0,0,,这将是重大挑战\N{\rEng}It will be the major challenge
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.28,0:48:45.24,中文,,0,0,0,,为了这一代和下一代。\N{\rEng}for this generation and the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.08,0:49:13.80,中文,,0,0,0,,拍摄影响\N{\rEng}To film the impact
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.80,0:49:15.92,中文,,0,0,0,,亚马逊雨林正在发生火灾，\N{\rEng}that fires are having on the Amazon,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.92,0:49:17.28,中文,,0,0,0,,地球脉动 III 团队\N{\rEng}the Planet Earth III team
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.28,0:49:20.96,中文,,0,0,0,,加入了当地的志愿消防队。\N{\rEng}joined a local volunteer fire brigade.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.00,0:49:25.24,中文,,0,0,0,,消防队正在响应补丁\N{\rEng}The fire brigade are responding to a patch
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.24,0:49:27.76,中文,,0,0,0,,正在燃烧的原始雨林。\N{\rEng}of primary rainforest that is burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.76,0:49:29.48,中文,,0,0,0,,现在已经烧了两天了。\N{\rEng}It's been burning for two days now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.48,0:49:32.28,中文,,0,0,0,,很难知道我们会看到什么。\N{\rEng}It's difficult to know what we're going to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.88,0:49:37.88,中文,,0,0,0,,火灾主要是非法纵火...\N{\rEng}The fires are mainly lit illegally...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.44,0:49:41.80,中文,,0,0,0,,...为牛清理空间。\N{\rEng}...to clear space for cattle.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.24,0:49:44.84,中文,,0,0,0,,真的很激烈
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.84,0:49:46.24,中文,,0,0,0,,看看那边的火
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.24,0:49:48.24,中文,,0,0,0,,我以前从未见过这样的事
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.24,0:49:51.64,中文,,0,0,0,,来吧，用水泵
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.64,0:49:54.14,中文,,0,0,0,,从远处做
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.14,0:49:56.84,中文,,0,0,0,,把拐角处的火停下来
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.56,0:50:01.64,中文,,0,0,0,,扑灭火灾是一项危险的工作。\N{\rEng}Battling fires is dangerous work.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.64,0:50:05.76,中文,,0,0,0,,但消防员每天都会面对他们。\N{\rEng}But the firefighters face them every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.24,0:50:09.28,中文,,0,0,0,,对于野生动物电影摄制组来说，\N{\rEng}For the wildlife film crew,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.28,0:50:12.24,中文,,0,0,0,,这是一种全新的体验。\N{\rEng}this is a totally new experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.24,0:50:17.16,中文,,0,0,0,,这些火灾可能是不可预测的。\N{\rEng}And these fires can be unpredictable.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.16,0:50:19.52,中文,,0,0,0,,尼尔，别在那里呆太久。\N{\rEng}Neil, don't spend long in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.44,0:50:25.86,中文,,0,0,0,,我们需要小心，这样火就不会烧到这里
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.86,0:50:28.86,中文,,0,0,0,,现在的风很危险
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.86,0:50:33.86,中文,,0,0,0,,我认为我们；我们得跑了
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.86,0:50:38.86,中文,,0,0,0,,我知道时间流逝
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.12,0:50:42.36,中文,,0,0,0,,哦！\N{\rEng}Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.86,0:50:47.34,中文,,0,0,0,,往这边跑
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.84,0:50:50.34,中文,,0,0,0,,这很可怕
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.60,0:50:55.40,中文,,0,0,0,,随着地面部队的撤退，\N{\rEng}With the ground team retreating,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.40,0:50:59.48,中文,,0,0,0,,最安全的拍摄方式是使用无人机。\N{\rEng}the safest way to carry on filming is with the drone.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.32,0:51:29.36,中文,,0,0,0,,我们失去了无人机吗？\N我想阿比已经看到了。\N{\rEng}Have we lost the drone? I think Abi has seen it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.36,0:51:30.56,中文,,0,0,0,,阿比正在赶来的路上。\N{\rEng}Abi is on her way.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.56,0:51:33.36,中文,,0,0,0,,阿比，你能确认你正在前往无人机的路上吗？\N{\rEng}Can you confirm you're on your way to the drone, Abi?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.40,0:51:37.99,中文,,0,0,0,,无人机已经起火
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.56,0:51:42.00,中文,,0,0,0,,男人喊叫\N{\rEng}MAN SHOUTS
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.24,0:51:46.76,中文,,0,0,0,,我有无人机
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.76,0:51:48.56,中文,,0,0,0,,它在我们面前坠毁了
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.56,0:51:50.56,中文,,0,0,0,,它着火了
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.04,0:51:55.40,中文,,0,0,0,,无人机已损坏且无法修复。\N{\rEng}The drone is damaged beyond repair.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.72,0:51:58.36,中文,,0,0,0,,别担心。\N我是认真的。\N{\rEng}Don't worry about it. I mean it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.36,0:52:01.00,中文,,0,0,0,,别担心。\N绝对没问题。\N{\rEng}Don't worry about it. It's absolutely fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.00,0:52:02.60,中文,,0,0,0,,这不行。\N这是。\N没关系。\N{\rEng}It's not OK. It is. It's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.60,0:52:04.32,中文,,0,0,0,,是装备啊\N我们有一个备用的。\N{\rEng}It's equipment. We've got a spare.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.32,0:52:06.96,中文,,0,0,0,,最重要的是，我们都很安全。\N没有人受伤。\N{\rEng}The main thing is, we're all safe. No-one's hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.64,0:52:11.56,中文,,0,0,0,,球队重新集结……\N{\rEng}The team regroup...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.52,0:52:15.96,中文,,0,0,0,,...并决定远离火源\N{\rEng}...and decide to move away from the heart of the fire
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.96,0:52:18.08,中文,,0,0,0,,到它的边缘\N{\rEng}to its fringes
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.08,0:52:21.24,中文,,0,0,0,,寻找被火焰困住的动物。\N{\rEng}to look for animals caught up in the flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.40,0:52:26.64,中文,,0,0,0,,有报道称树上有一只猴子，所以...\N{\rEng}There's been reports of a monkey in the trees, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.00,0:52:29.00,中文,,0,0,0,,啊!\N{\rEng}Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.00,0:52:31.28,中文,,0,0,0,,他们说葡萄牙语\N{\rEng}THEY SPEAK PORTUGUESE
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.28,0:52:33.52,中文,,0,0,0,,问题是这里一路上都着火\N{\rEng}The problem is, there's fires all the way along here,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.52,0:52:35.92,中文,,0,0,0,,以及一直在这里，所以...\N{\rEng}as well as all along here, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.92,0:52:38.08,中文,,0,0,0,,很难知道这些野生动物会做什么\N{\rEng}It's hard to know what all this wildlife is going to do
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.08,0:52:40.40,中文,,0,0,0,,当他们的家被烧成这样的时候。\N{\rEng}when their home is burnt up like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.32,0:52:46.36,中文,,0,0,0,,我不知道这些雨林动物的感受如何\N{\rEng}I don't know what it's like for these rainforest animals
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.36,0:52:47.84,中文,,0,0,0,,遭遇火灾。\N{\rEng}to be experiencing a fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.84,0:52:49.76,中文,,0,0,0,,这对我来说太可怕了，所以...\N{\rEng}It's horrific for me, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.84,0:52:53.48,中文,,0,0,0,,……我不知道这对他们来说意味着什么。\N{\rEng}...I don't know what it is for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.00,0:53:00.08,中文,,0,0,0,,大火一直燃烧到深夜。\N{\rEng}The fires burn into the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.08,0:53:14.12,中文,,0,0,0,,第二天，\N{\rEng}The following day,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.12,0:53:17.04,中文,,0,0,0,,船员陪同消防员\N{\rEng}the crew accompany the firefighters
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.04,0:53:20.84,中文,,0,0,0,,灾后寻找动物的过程中。\N{\rEng}in the search for animals in the aftermath.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.24,0:53:25.00,中文,,0,0,0,,天哪，里面全是火焰。\N{\rEng}Oh, my God, there are flames all inside of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.00,0:53:26.68,中文,,0,0,0,,小白蚁...\N{\rEng}Little termite...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.20,0:53:30.28,中文,,0,0,0,,我的天啊！\N{\rEng}Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.00,0:53:36.04,中文,,0,0,0,,值得注意的是，一些动物幸存下来。\N{\rEng}Remarkably, some animals have survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.80,0:53:49.04,中文,,0,0,0,,对我来说很痛苦
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.54,0:53:55.84,中文,,0,0,0,,因为大自然是有生命的，就像我们一样
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.84,0:53:59.84,中文,,0,0,0,,我们所拥有的一切，它也拥有
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.99,0:54:06.84,中文,,0,0,0,,所以看到这样的森林很难过
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.84,0:54:15.10,中文,,0,0,0,,受罚应该！但不应该这样对待
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.80,0:54:18.80,中文,,0,0,0,,它一定很强壮
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.80,0:54:22.80,中文,,0,0,0,,给我们力量
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.80,0:54:27.80,中文,,0,0,0,,因为如果它变弱，我们就会感觉更弱
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.80,0:54:30.80,中文,,0,0,0,,如果它倒下了，我们都会倒下
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.40,0:54:35.24,中文,,0,0,0,,清理土地用于农业\N{\rEng}Clearing land for farming
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.24,0:54:37.72,中文,,0,0,0,,这并不是亚马逊独有的问题。\N{\rEng}is not a problem unique to the Amazon.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.80,0:54:43.64,中文,,0,0,0,,农业现在占据了一半的可居住土地\N{\rEng}Agriculture now takes up half of the habitable land
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.64,0:54:45.52,中文,,0,0,0,,在这个星球上。\N{\rEng}on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.36,0:54:50.32,中文,,0,0,0,,生产对自然世界影响较小的食品\N{\rEng}To produce food with less impact on the natural world
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.32,0:54:53.20,中文,,0,0,0,,需要新的方法。\N{\rEng}requires new approaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.40,0:54:58.36,中文,,0,0,0,,这让野生动物电影摄制组来到了一个农场\N{\rEng}And that led the wildlife film crew to a farm
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.36,0:55:00.52,中文,,0,0,0,,在一个仓库里。\N{\rEng}in a warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.04,0:55:06.88,中文,,0,0,0,,我们在市中心！\N{\rEng}We're in the middle of the city!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.88,0:55:09.08,中文,,0,0,0,,我简直不敢相信有这么多食物\N{\rEng}I can't believe so much food
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.08,0:55:11.60,中文,,0,0,0,,竟然在这么小的空间里生长！\N{\rEng}being grown in such a small space!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.40,0:55:18.88,中文,,0,0,0,,在距离亚马逊 6,000 英里的洛杉矶，\N{\rEng}Here in Los Angeles, 6,000 miles from the Amazon,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.88,0:55:22.52,中文,,0,0,0,,这个农场是蓬勃发展的食品革命的一部分。\N{\rEng}this farm is part of a burgeoning food revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.00,0:55:27.32,中文,,0,0,0,,这是世界上生产力最高的农场，\N{\rEng}This is the most productive farm in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.32,0:55:30.08,中文,,0,0,0,,我们的目标是减少土地和资源的数量\N{\rEng}and it's our goal to reduce the amount of land and resources
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.08,0:55:32.48,中文,,0,0,0,,必须增长到最低限度。\N{\rEng}necessary to grow down to the bare minimum.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.48,0:55:34.92,中文,,0,0,0,,我花了一段时间才明白，对于大自然来说，\N{\rEng}It took a while to understand that, for nature,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.92,0:55:36.96,中文,,0,0,0,,农业用地\N{\rEng}agricultural use of land
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.96,0:55:40.64,中文,,0,0,0,,是人类主要的破坏性行为。\N{\rEng}was the primary, like, destructive behaviour of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.64,0:55:43.84,中文,,0,0,0,,当我们扩大这种增长方式时，\N{\rEng}As we expand this means of growing,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.84,0:55:47.00,中文,,0,0,0,,我非常希望这种方法最终能够\N{\rEng}I'm very hopeful that this approach can ultimately
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.00,0:55:49.24,中文,,0,0,0,,让大量土地回归自然\N{\rEng}give a lot of land back to nature
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.24,0:55:52.04,中文,,0,0,0,,并让生物多样性得以重建和繁荣。\N{\rEng}and allow that biodiversity to re-establish and flourish.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.36,0:55:57.84,中文,,0,0,0,,这个农场不仅占用的空间更少......\N{\rEng}Not only does this farm use less space...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.04,0:56:03.24,中文,,0,0,0,,...但它的用水量也减少了 90%，\N{\rEng}...but it also uses 90% less water,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.24,0:56:05.64,中文,,0,0,0,,没有农药，\N{\rEng}no pesticides,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.64,0:56:08.04,中文,,0,0,0,,并减少食物里程。\N{\rEng}and cuts food miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.68,0:56:13.64,中文,,0,0,0,,这确实感觉像是一个很好的开始。\N{\rEng}It does feel like a really good start.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.64,0:56:19.84,中文,,0,0,0,,像这样的想法可以减少我们在地球上的足迹，\N{\rEng}Ideas like this can reduce our footprint on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.84,0:56:24.64,中文,,0,0,0,,给自然世界一个反弹的机会。\N{\rEng}giving the natural world a chance to bounce back.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.92,0:56:35.68,中文,,0,0,0,,下次，\N{\rEng}Next time,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.68,0:56:39.64,中文,,0,0,0,,奋战在前线拯救野生动物的英雄们。\N{\rEng}the heroes on the frontline saving wildlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.28,0:56:45.12,中文,,0,0,0,,他们正在探索偏远的丛林......\N{\rEng}They're exploring remote jungles...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.88,0:56:50.20,中文,,0,0,0,,...卧底抓捕罪犯...\N{\rEng}...working undercover to catch criminals...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.72,0:56:55.12,中文,,0,0,0,,...并将濒临灭绝的生物引导到安全的地方。\N{\rEng}...and leading endangered creatures to safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.08,0:57:02.28,中文,,0,0,0,,栖息地探索者让动物及其栖息地栩栩如生。\N{\rEng}Habitat Explorer brings animals and their habitats to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.28,0:57:05.92,中文,,0,0,0,,探索这个免费的互动并制作折纸动物。\N{\rEng}Explore this free interactive and make origami animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.92,0:57:10.00,中文,,0,0,0,,去...\N{\rEng}Go to...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.00,0:57:12.24,中文,,0,0,0,,...然后点击开放大学的链接。\N{\rEng}...and follow the links to the Open University.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.24,0:57:15.64,中文,,0,0,0,,或者要订购免费印刷版，请访问网站\N{\rEng}Or to order a free printed version, visit the website
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.64,0:57:18.24,中文,,0,0,0,,或拨打屏幕上的号码。\N{\rEng}or call the number on the screen.

